sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861162
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for cAMP receptor protein(CRP; also known as catabolite activator protein, CAP). cAMP receptor protein is a DNA-binding transcriptional dual regulator in bacteria. CRP protein binds cAMP.;which causes a conformational change that allows CRP to bind tightly to a specific DNA site in the promoters of the genes it controls. This device contains a constitutive promoter J23116 .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Xian Xia, Kuanwei Sheng

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861175
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: Efficacy testing RFP generator of BBa_K861170 (PI)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: PI is a promoter designed for the Eschaerichia coli . It includes the CRP-binding site and the RNA polymerase-binding site which have a overlap of several base pairs.Therefore due to the steric hindrance between CRP and RNA polymerase,gene downstream of the promoter will be repressed at high concentration of CRP.In the cells ,low glucose concentration results in increased activity by adenylate cyclase. cAMP binds to the cAMP receptor protein, which, in its bound form, is able to bind tightly to the specific DNA site in the promoter and repress the gene downstream.On the contrary,high glucose concentration will result in the expression of the promoter.This device contains PI and a screening plasmid intermediate .
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Kuanwei Shneg, Xian Xia

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_K861170
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Escherichia coli str. K-12 substr. MG1655
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: This is a promoter designed for the Eschaerichia coli . It includes the CRP-binding site and the RNA polymerase-binding site which have a overlap of several base pairs.So because of the steric hindrance between CRP and RNA polymerase,gene downstream of the promoter will be repressed at high concentration of CRP.In the cells ,low glucose concentration results in increased activity by adenylate cyclase. cAMP binds to the cAMP receptor protein, which, in its bound form, is able to bind tightly to the specific DNA site in the promoter and repress the gene downstream.On the contrary,high glucose concentration will result in the expression of the promoter.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0034
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix.

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info for this part: Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Randy Rettberg

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: mRFP1
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: **highly** engineered mutant of red fluorescent protein from Discosoma striata (coral)
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Campbell et al., PNAS v99 p7877 URL
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: monomeric RFP: Red Fluorescent Protein. Excitation peak: 584 nm Emission peak: 607 nm
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
TAATAA double stop codon added (DE).
Four silent mutations made to remove three EcoRI sites and one PstI site: A28G, A76G, A349G, G337A.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Drew Endy

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0030
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Strong RBS based on Ron Weiss thesis. Strength is considered relative to <bb_part>BBa_B0031</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0032</bb_part>, <bb_part>BBa_B0033</bb_part>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Varies from -6 to +1 region from original sequence to accomodate BioBricks suffix ("orig" in figure 4-14 of Ron Weiss thesis).

No secondary structures are formed in the given RBS region. Users should check for secondary structures induced in the RBS by upstream and downstream elements in the +50 to -50 region, as such structures will greatly affect the strength of the RBS. Contact info Brian Chow
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Vinay S Mahajan, Voichita D. Marinescu, Brian Chow, Alexander D Wissner-Gross and Peter Carr IAP, 2003.
